# Blender's OBJ exporter (tools/gen_vehicle.py, tools/gen_buildings.py) uses platform line
# endings, so kit regeneration churned these CRLF<->LF against the LF index whenever
# core.autocrlf flipped the working copies. The .vmdl/.vmat writers already emit LF, so only
# the exporter-written .obj/.mtl need pinning. Pin them to LF (matching the index) so a
# regen produces no EOL-only diff.
*.obj text eol=lf
*.mtl text eol=lf
